<TITLE> Khaleda to be kept in special jail: official </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 3 (bdnews24.com) -- Former prime minister Khaleda Zia will be kept in a special jail on the Jatiya Sangsad Bhaban premises, said IG (prisons) brigadier general Zakir Hasan. The BNP chairperson will be held in the house reserved for the speaker of parliament, Hasan told bdnews24.com early Monday. But her son Arafat Rahman Coco will be kept in Dhaka Central Jail, he added. The former prime minister and her son were arrested shortly after 7:30am Monday. They were brought to the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka. The Anticorruption Commission filed a case Sunday against Khaleda, her son and 11 others on allegations of irregularities in appointing a contractor for the Inland Container Depot in Kamalapur and Chittagong Port Container Terminal. bdnews24.co
